<div class="grid">
  <div class="grid__item three-fifths lap-one-half palm-one-whole">
    <p class="lead">There is a section at the foot of the search form called <em>Additional Search options</em> — these will help you with those tricky-to-find records, by adding power and flexibility to your search. The additional options give you access to what are known as partial searches.</p>
    <p>We are confident that once you try these options a few times, you will soon get the hang of how they work. But, if you are not finding what you expect to find, we hope that the information here will help you understand what is going on and have success with searching.</p>
    <p><strong>Partial searches</strong> work on what you enter in one of the name boxes in the search form: in First Names, Surname or Mother’s Surname. The search looks for those names that include what you put in one of the name boxes in some way, as long as you type at least three letters and do not use symbols.</p>
    <p>There are just two boxes in the Additional search options: the <em>Choose the Name field</em> box lets you select which part of the name to look at; the second box, labelled <em>Select one of the following</em> lets you choose the type of partial search.</p>      
  </div>

